Determines computer user needs; advises hardware designers on machine characteristics that affect software systems such as storage capacity, processing speed, and input/output requirements; designs and develops compilers and assemblers, utility programs, and operating systems.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Eight (8) years of experience in the analysis, planning, design, development, installation, reengineering, and/or support of integrated systems. Knowledgeable of software engineering concepts, principles, methods, processes and procedures.

labor_categories.years_experience: Eight (8) years of experience in the analysis, planning, design, development, installation, reengineering, and/or support of integrated systems. Knowledgeable of software engineering concepts, principles, methods, processes and procedures.

raw_data.title: Software Engineer  Associate
raw_data.description: Under direct supervision, assists in designing and developing compilers and assemblers, utility programs, and operating systems.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Zero (0) to two (2) years of experience in the analysis, planning, design, development, installation, reengineering, and/or support of integrated systems. Knowledgeable of software engineering concepts, principles, methods, processes and procedures.

labor_categories.years_experience: Zero (0) to two (2) years of experience in the analysis, planning, design, development, installation, reengineering, and/or support of integrated systems. Knowledgeable of software engineering concepts, principles, methods, processes and procedures.
